article.headline: UTEP 79, Louisiana-Monroe 49
article.story: EL PASO, Texas -- Randy Culpepper had 18 points and every starter for UTEP scored in double figures as the Miners coasted to a 79-49 victory over Louisiana-Monroe on Wednesday night. Jeremy Williams and Claude Britten each added 14 points for UTEP (7-2), which won its fourth straight. Fabio Ribeiro came off the bench to lead the Warhawks (3-8) with 15 points, and Hugh Mingo had 11. Christian Polk's 3-pointer with 9:34 left in the first half gave the Miners their first double-digit lead, 23-13, and started a 12-0 run. UTEP pushed its advantage to 40-19 at intermission and led by at least 20 the entire second half. Polk finished with 12 points and Julyan Stone had 10.
